  "text": "Although an overall analysis did not show a significant difference in ICARS, FARS, or ADL total scores, a statistical test for trend (Jonckheere) indicated dosedependent improvement in ICARS. A second, pre-specified analysis, excluding patients who required wheelchair assistance, showed a significant improvement in ICARS and a dose-dependent improvement in ICARS, FARS, and ADL with idebenone treatment. For these functional scales, the data indicated that neither placebo nor low-dose idebenone had an effect, whereas intermediate and high doses of idebenone significantly improved the scores, with little difference observed among the latter two groups. In the pre-specified analysis, scores in the intermediate-dose and high-dose groups improved by approximately 4.3 and 5.8 points, respectively, on the ICARS scale and by 5.2 and 5.1 points on the FARS [CITATION_1] .",
